<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1063" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1063">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.01/5–1245</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Lebanese Minister</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Malik</hi></persName>)<note n="40" xml:id="d1063fn40">Sent by the Director of the Office of Near
                                Eastern and African Affairs on May 24 to the Deputy Director of that
                                Office for delivery to Dr. Malik at San Francisco.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-24">May 24,
                                1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of May 12, 1945, in which you bring to my attention
                            certain information which you have received from your Government in
                            regard to the proposed landing of French relief forces at Beirut.</p>
                        <p>This Government is aware of the circumstances referred to in your note
                            and is giving the matter its careful attention, and earnestly hopes <pb facs="1110" n="1098" xml:id="pg_1098"/> that a solution may be
                            reached which will be satisfactory to the Government of the Lebanese
                            Republic.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph</hi> C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>